  "texts": [
    "here, i t, f t, and o t represent the input, forget, and output gates, respectively, and c t is the cell state (Staudemeyer and Morris 2019).",
    "The gates are controlled by the sigmoid activation function to regulate the flow of information and maintain gradients through long sequences (Schmidt 2019).",
    "In the context of fossil image analysis, RNNs can be applied to sequential images of a single microfossil taken from various angles or under different conditions (Ozer et al. 2023; Hou et al. 2020).",
    "For instance, RNNs can help improve classification accuracy by analyzing the temporal sequence of images, allowing the model to capture subtle morphological variations that might not be apparent in a single image.",
    "This approach can be particularly valuable in distinguishing between closely related microfossil species, where minute differences in structure are critical for accurate identification."
  ]
